datasets.name: b3e86a40
datasets.query:
with ranked_logs as (
    select 
        `timestamp`,
        request_id,
        source.id as source_id,
        text_assessment.ratings["answer_correct"]["value"] as text_rating,
        retrieval_assessment.ratings["answer_correct"]["value"] as retrieval_rating,
        retrieval_assessment.position as retrieval_position,
        row_number() over (
            partition by request_id, source.id, retrieval_assessment.position order by `timestamp` desc
        ) as rank
    from {{assessment_log_table_name}}
), human_assessments as (
    select 
        `timestamp`,
        request_id as databricks_request_id,
        source_id,
        text_rating,
        case
            when retrieval_rating = "false" then "negative"
            when retrieval_rating = "true" then "positive"
            when retrieval_rating = "i_dont_know" then "i_dont_know"
            else null
        end as retrieval_rating,
        retrieval_position
    from ranked_logs
    where rank = 1
    order by `timestamp` desc
), aggregated_human_assessments as (
    select 
        databricks_request_id,
        sum(case when text_rating = 'positive' then 1 else 0 end) as positive_text_ratings,
        sum(case when text_rating = 'negative' or text_rating = 'i_dont_know' then 1 else 0 end) as negative_text_ratings,
        sum(case when retrieval_rating = 'positive' then 1 else 0 end) as positive_retrieval_ratings,
        sum(case when retrieval_rating = 'negative' or retrieval_rating = 'i_dont_know' then 1 else 0 end) as negative_retrieval_ratings
    from human_assessments
    group by databricks_request_id
), eval_log as (
    select 
        *,
        execution_time_ms / 1000 as execution_time_s,
        concat(
            '/ml/experiments/',
            experiment_id,
            '/runs/',
            run_id,
            '/evaluations?searchQuery=',
            databricks_request_id
        ) as eval_details
    from {{eval_requests_log_table_name}}
    where 
        run_id is not null 
        and run_id != "skipped"
)
select
    eval_log.*,
    case 
        when negative_text_ratings = 0 and positive_text_ratings = 0 then null
        when negative_text_ratings >= positive_text_ratings then "negative" 
        when negative_text_ratings < positive_text_ratings then "positive" 
        else null
    end as user_text_rating,
    case 
        when negative_retrieval_ratings = 0 and positive_retrieval_ratings = 0 then null
        when negative_retrieval_ratings >= positive_retrieval_ratings then "negative" 
        when negative_retrieval_ratings < positive_retrieval_ratings then "positive" 
        else null
    end as user_retrieval_rating
from eval_log
left join aggregated_human_assessments 
on eval_log.databricks_request_id = aggregated_human_assessments.databricks_request_id

        retrieval_assessment.position as retrieval_position,

        source_id,
        text_rating,
        case
            when retrieval_rating = "false" then "negative"
            when retrieval_rating = "true" then "positive"
            when retrieval_rating = "i_dont_know" then "i_dont_know"
            else null
        end as retrieval_rating,
        retrieval_position
    from ranked_logs
    where rank = 1
    order by `timestamp` desc
), aggregated_human_assessments as (
    select 
        databricks_request_id,
        sum(case when text_rating = 'positive' then 1 else 0 end) as positive_text_ratings,
        sum(case when text_rating = 'negative' or text_rating = 'i_dont_know' then 1 else 0 end) as negative_text_ratings,
        sum(case when retrieval_rating = 'positive' then 1 else 0 end) as positive_retrieval_ratings,
        sum(case when retrieval_rating = 'negative' or retrieval_rating = 'i_dont_know' then 1 else 0 end) as negative_retrieval_ratings
    from human_assessments
    group by databricks_request_id
)
select
    eval_log.*,
    case 
        when negative_text_ratings = 0 and positive_text_ratings = 0 then null
        when negative_text_ratings >= positive_text_ratings then "negative" 
        when negative_text_ratings < positive_text_ratings then "positive" 
        else null
    end as user_text_rating,
    case 
        when negative_retrieval_ratings = 0 and positive_retrieval_ratings = 0 then null
        when negative_retrieval_ratings >= positive_retrieval_ratings then "negative" 
        when negative_retrieval_ratings < positive_retrieval_ratings then "positive" 
        else null
    end as user_retrieval_rating
from (
    select *
    from {{eval_requests_log_table_name}}
    where run_id is not null 
) eval_log
left join aggregated_human_assessments 
on eval_log.databricks_request_id = aggregated_human_assessments.databricks_request_id

frame.title: Breakdown of safety
frame.description: A response is safe (yes) if it does not include harmful content.

frame.title: Breakdown of groundedness
frame.description: A response is grounded (yes) when its content is derived entirely from the retrieved context. Otherwise (no) it contains hallucinations.

frame.title: Breakdown of response relevance
frame.description: A relevant response (yes) is useful in answering the input request.

frame.title: Average judged precision
frame.description: Judged precision is the percentage of retrieved chunks that are relevant to the request.
